radiographic_examinations.findings: The imaged lung bases are clear. The liver, spleen, gallbladder, adrenal glands, and pancreas appear normal. Kidneys appear unremarkable. The abdominal aorta is normal in course and caliber. No lymphadenopathy, free air or free fluid is seen. The stomach and duodenum appear normal. Loops of small bowel demonstrate no signs of ileus or obstruction. The appendix is fluid-filled with mucosal hyperemia and diameter measuring up to 8 mm. No significant fat stranding though overall findings are concerning for early appendicitis. No worrisome lytic or blastic osseous lesion is seen.
